# Below are the main config files for ansible to run
    1. ansible.cfg
    2. inventory file
    3. .ansible-navigator.yml
    4. playbook
    5. ~/.vimrc

# Ansible config file:
Default file location of this file is /etc/ansible/ansible.cfg
But best practice is to create a config file in side each ansible project

Sample config file

[defaults]
inventory = path/to/the/inventory/file
remote_user = username
ask_pass = true/false

[privilege_escalations]
become = true/false
become_method = sudo/su
become_user = username
become_ask_pass = false

# Inventory file
We can define the inventory path inside ansible.cfg file
by default it will take the /etc/hosts/hosts file for inventory

Sample config file

[prod]                              #groups will be configure in this brackets
10.10.10.21                         #Hosts under this group
10.10.10.22

[test]
10.10.10.23

[dev]
10.10.10.24

[devops:children]                   #groups with sub/children groups 
prod                                #group names under the devops group
dev

# ~/.ansible-navigator.yml file
This file will be configured inside the user home dorectory, 
This contains the navigator configuration details,

Sample ~/.ansible-navigator.yml file

---
    ansible-navigator:
        execution-environment:
            image: image name along with the FQCN (Fully Qualified Container Name) address
            pull:
                policy: missing
    playbook-artifact:
        enabled: false

# Playbook
Playbook is a yaml language file which consists of plays and tasks
Playbook Consists of multiple plays and multiple tasks under one play

play books are written in YAML language: YET ANOTHER MARKUP LANGUAGE
# YAML:-
it always starts with ---
it contains lists, information, sub-information
it contains the information in lists 
And All List parameters are starts with '-' and information will not contain - in starting
And sub-information will have more white space Than the information line
for Ex:
data:
- name      - age       - state
    ansible     32          karnataka
    redhat      23              bengaluru
    terraform   64          Telangana
    jenkins     56              hyderabad

    In YAML: 
       - name               # list
            ansible
            redhat
            terraform
            jenkins         # information
       
       - age                # list
            32
            23
            64
            56              # information
       
       - state              # list
            karnataka       # information
                bengaluru   # sub-information (more white space)
            telangana       # information
                hyderabad   # sub-information (more white space)

# Sample Playbook

---
  - name: create folder and file
    hosts: devops
    tasks:
      - name: create a file
        ansible.builtin.file:
            path: /home/student/first-folder
            state: directory
      - name: create a file
        ansible.builtin.file:
            path: /home/student/first-file
            state: touch

